## CRUD Generation

- Directory layout per module:
  - Views in `src/views/<module>/` e.g., `list.vue`, `create.vue`, `edit.vue` and `components/Form.vue`.
  - API in `src/api/<module>.js` using the Axios wrapper.
- List page requirements:
  - Search bar using `<el-form inline>`; reset sets `page=1`.
  - Table using `<el-table :data="rows" v-loading="loading" border fit>`.
  - Actions column with edit/delete buttons; protect with `v-permission` where needed.
  - Pagination via `src/components/Pagination` with `v-model:page` and `v-model:limit` and `@pagination="getList"`.
- Dialog or sub-view for create/edit:
  - Prefer reusable `<Form>` component embedded in `<el-dialog>` for quick workflows.
  - Use `<el-form :model="form" :rules="rules" ref="formRef">` and validate on submit.
- Element Plus validation:
  - Use `{ required: true, message: 'Requerido', trigger: 'blur'|'change' }` per field.
- Minimal API interface:
  - `fetchList(params)`, `fetchOne(id)`, `create(data)`, `update(id, data)`, `remove(id)` returning `{ code, data }` as in [src/utils/request.js](mdc:src/utils/request.js).
- Example usage exists in [src/views/example/list.vue](mdc:src/views/example/list.vue) and [src/components/Pagination](mdc:src/components/Pagination/index.vue).
